    	<h1>PGA Perceptions from the Middle Kingdom</h1>
    	<h2>Current Trends and Developments in Chinese Aviation</h2>

        <!-- Listing Start -->
        <div class="row margin-top">
          <div class="col-md-12">
                <div class="portfolio-header">2019 February Report</div>
                <div class="portfolio-subheader"><a href="Documents/2019 February Report - PGA Aviation.pdf" target="_blank">Impending Major Changes in PRC Aviation Industry Organization and Structure</a></div>
            	<p>Top-down directed changes with global impact would revolutionize Chinese aviation in ways that wouldn't be possible elsewhere.</p>
              <a class="btn portfolio-btn" href="Documents/2019 February Report - PGA Aviation.pdf" target="_blank">Open 2019 February Report (PDF)</a>
            </div>
        </div> 
        
        <!-- Listing Start -->
        <div class="row margin-top">
          <div class="col-md-12">
                <div class="portfolio-header">2018 Q3 Report</div>
                <div class="portfolio-subheader"><a href="Documents/2018 Q3 Report - PGA Aviation.pdf" target="_blank">Impact of Sino/US Trade Dispute on PRC Commercial Aircraft and Engine Purchases</a></div>
            	<p>The current "trade war" between the US and China is less likely to significantly impact airplane and engine sales than the mass media and some on Wall Street seem to think it will.</p>
              <a class="btn portfolio-btn" href="Documents/2018 Q3 Report - PGA Aviation.pdf" target="_blank">Open 2018 Q3 Report (PDF)</a>
            </div>
        </div> 
		
        <!-- Listing Start -->
        <div class="row margin-top">
          <div class="col-md-12">
                <div class="portfolio-header">2017 Q4 Report</div>
                <div class="portfolio-subheader"><a href="Documents/2017 Q4 Report - PGA Aviation.pdf" target="_blank">China Thirty Years Later: Fleet and the Challenges Have Matured</a></div>
            	<p>During the past 30 years, the Chinese western-built mainline commercial passenger aircraft fleet has grown from about 50 aircraft in May 1988, to about 2,600 aircraft today. This is an extraordinary accomplishment which has revolutionized transportation within China and globally.</p>
              <a class="btn portfolio-btn" href="Documents/2017 Q4 Report - PGA Aviation.pdf" target="_blank">Open 2017 Q4 Report (PDF)</a>
            </div>
        </div> 

        <!-- Listing Start -->
        <div class="row margin-top">
          <div class="col-md-12">
                <div class="portfolio-header">2017 Q3 Report</div>
                <div class="portfolio-subheader"><a href="Documents/2017 Q3 Report - PGA Aviation.pdf" target="_blank">Fleet Phaseout Plans</a></div>
            <p>The recent multi-airline "package deal" for a large quantity of new aircraft, announced during the U.S. presidential visit to China, is another example of the existing triangle relationship between Chinese Airlines, both major western OEMs and the PRC government.</p>
              <a class="btn portfolio-btn" href="Documents/2017 Q3 Report - PGA Aviation.pdf" target="_blank">Open 2017 Q3 Report (PDF)</a>
            </div>
        </div> 

        <!-- Listing Start -->
        <div class="row margin-top">
          <div class="col-md-12">
                <div class="portfolio-header">2017 Q2 Report</div>
                <div class="portfolio-subheader"><a href="Documents/2017 Q2 Report - PGA Aviation.pdf" target="_blank">Chinese cargo airlines and e-commerce volume</a></div>
            <p>Chinese cargo airlines ride growing wave of e-commerce volume, but are inhibited by shortage of additional new and converted freighters.</p>
              <a class="btn portfolio-btn" href="Documents/2017 Q2 Report - PGA Aviation.pdf" target="_blank">Open 2017 Q2 Report (PDF)</a>
            </div>
        </div> 

        <div class="row margin-top">
            <div class="col-md-12">
                <div class="portfolio-header">2017 Q1 Report</div>
                <div class="portfolio-subheader"><a href="Documents/2017 Q1 Report - PGA Aviation.pdf" target="_blank">Package Deals</a></div>
                <p>We anticipate that the forthcoming new rules will address several fundamental issues while presumably (hopefully?) also promoting harmony, at least in the long run, among Chinese governmental agencies, Chinese airlines, and foreign airplane OEMs.</p>
                <a class="btn portfolio-btn" href="/Documents/2017 Q1 Report - PGA Aviation.pdf" target="_blank">Open 2017 Q1 Report (PDF)</a>
            </div>
        </div> 
        
        <div class="row margin-top">
          <div class="col-md-12">
                <div class="portfolio-header">2016 Q4 Report</div>
                <div class="portfolio-subheader"><a href="Documents/2016 Q4 Report - PGA Aviation.pdf" target="_blank">2016 Year-End Status of Taiwanese Scheduled Carriers</a></div>
              <p>Although Taiwan is a small island, it is strategically well 
                  positioned geographically to serve as a world hub for the 
                  trans-Pacific and South Asian long-haul markets, which 
                  greatly favors the established local entrants China Airlines 
              and EVA with their combined long-haul and regional fleets.</p>
              <a class="btn portfolio-btn" href="Documents/2016 Q4 Report - PGA Aviation.pdf" target="_blank">Open 2016 Q4 Report (PDF)</a>
            </div>
        </div> 

        <div class="row margin-top">
            <div class="col-md-12">
                <div class="portfolio-header">2016 Q3 Report</div>
                <div class="portfolio-subheader"><a href="Documents/2016 Q3 Report - PGA Aviation.pdf" target="_blank">New CAAC Internal Policy Rule Makes Market Entry More Difficult For Domestic Startup Airlines</a></div>
                <p>Perhaps the most significant Q3 development for the PRC domestic aviation industry was the issuance of CAAC Internal Rule #96 dated August 29, 2016 governing the process for market entry by new startup airlines (hereinafter "the Rule").</p>
                <a class="btn portfolio-btn" href="/Documents/2016 Q3 Report - PGA Aviation.pdf" target="_blank">Open 2016 Q3 Report (PDF)</a>
            </div>
        </div> 
        
        <div class="row margin-top">
            <div class="col-md-12">
                <div class="portfolio-header">2016 Q2 Report</div>
                <div class="portfolio-subheader"><a href="Documents/2016 Q2 Report - PGA Aviation.pdf" target="_blank">Q2 Government Approvals of Pending Deliveries Continue On Pace But May Be Impacted By Evolving Circumstances Going Forward</a></div>
                <p>We continue to witness steady growth within China's airline industry, despite a challenging business climate in other industries, in China as well as worldwide.</p>
                <a class="btn portfolio-btn" href="/Documents/2016 Q2 Report - PGA Aviation.pdf" target="_blank">Open 2016 Q2 Report (PDF)</a>
            </div>
		</div>
        
       <div class="row margin-top">
            <div class="col-md-12">
                <div class="portfolio-header">2016 Q1 Report</div>
                <div class="portfolio-subheader"><a href="Documents/2016 Q1 Report - PGA Aviation.pdf" target="_blank">New PRC Government Regulatory Requirements Will Complicate Used Aircraft Transactions</a></div>
                <p>The past few years have seen a robust purchase and expansion phase for both mainland China network carriers and China's newly developed bank-owned operating lessors. The Chinese airlines are continuing to place large orders with western OEMs, whether through stand-alone deals or by participation in a multi-airline &quot;package&quot; deal under PRC Government supervision...</p>
                <a class="btn portfolio-btn" href="Documents/2016 Q1 Report - PGA Aviation.pdf" target="_blank">Open 2016 Q1 Report (PDF)</a>
            </div>
        </div>
